org.sbml.jsbml.validator.offline

Class LoggingValidationContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbml.jsbml.validator.offline.ValidationContext
      • org.sbml.jsbml.validator.offline.LoggingValidationContext
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ValidationListener

    public class LoggingValidationContext
extends ValidationContext
implements ValidationListener
    A subclass of ValidationContext which implements the ValidationListener interface to track his own validation process.

    An instance of this class creates an SBMLErrorLog which contains some SBMLError object for every broken constraint.

    The level and version parameter are used to determine which rules will be checked.

    For more informations about the SBML specifications look up sbml.org .

    Since:
    1.2
    Author:
    Roman, rodrigue

      • analyseSBMLerrorLog

        public static java.util.Set<java.lang.String> analyseSBMLerrorLog(java.util.List<SBMLError> validationErrors)
        Goes through the list of SBMLError given to determined which check categories should be ignored.

        As soon as an error is detected in a check category, all the categories below it should be ignored. The order of the check category is:

        • identifier consistency
        • general consistency
        • sbo consistency
        • math consistency
        • units consistency
        • overdetermined consistency
        • modelling practice

        Parameters:
        validationErrors - the list of SBMLError to check
        Returns:
        a set of check categories that should be ignored.
